        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="11">
            <title>Service procedure</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove four screws holding the instrument cluster in the dash (one screw at each
                    corner). Pull cluster forward and disconnect three electrical connectors plus air and oil lines from
                    the rear of the cluster. Remove the cluster from the dash.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <para>Refer to INSTRUMENT PANEL REMOVAL in GROUP 08 of the Service Manual for detailed information for
                removing dash panel sections.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove right lower section of the dash panel cover.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove screws that hold the right section of the dash panel cover in place. Slide the
                    right panel out from under the left section and remove the right panel.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the ash tray, ash tray track and light harness (if equipped).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove screws that hold the left dash panel in place and remove the left dash panel.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove screws that hold the defroster cover in place and remove the defroster cover.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two rivets that fasten the intermediate duct to the cowl panel. Remove the old
                    duct (Figure 1) and discard.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f9016081" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9016081.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Intermediate Duct Removal</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the adhesive backing from the cowl panel cover (item 6, Parts List) and place
                    over the left duct outlet hole in the cowl panel, in front of the steering wheel (Figure 2).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f9016082" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9016082.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Cowl Panel Opening Cover</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Cut out the template as indicated on sheet one of Part Number 1,087,500R1 (Parts
                    List).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the template in position on the cowl panel as illustrated in Figure 3 with TAB "A"
                    lined up in the offset of the cowl.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f9016083" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9016083.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. TAB "A" of Template</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Scribe the hole outline in the template onto the cowl panel.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>When cutting the hole, care must be taken to not cut the cab wiring.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Cut the scribed hole into the cowl panel.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the adhesive cover from the two cowl opening seals (Items 3 and 4, Parts List).
                    Place the left seal around the new opening on the left hand side of the cowl (Figure 4) and the
                    right seal around the right hand opening in the cowl panel (Figure 5).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f9016084" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9016084.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px"/>
                <caption>Figure 4. Left Side Cowl Seal</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f9016085" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9016085.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px"/>
                <caption>Figure 5. Right Side Cowl Seal</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove both air deflectors from the defroster cover.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inside the right hand side of the defroster cover, completely remove the ridge that
                    surrounded the air deflector opening (Figure 6).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f9016086" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9016086.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px"/>
                <caption>Figure 6. Remove Ridge - Right Side</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">On the left hand side of the defroster cover, remove 8 inches of the ridge inside the
                    air deflector opening (Figure 7).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f9016087" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9016087.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px"/>
                <caption>Figure 7. Remove Ridge - Left Side</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Cut out both templates (right and left hand) from sheet two of part number 1,087,500R1
                    (Item 11, Parts List).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the left hand template over the left deflector opening and the right hand template
                    over the right deflector opening of the defroster cover (Figure 8). Drill two #10 holes through the
                    defroster cover as instructed on the templates.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place both air deflectors in the defrost cover (Figure 9 and 10).
                    <emph type="bold">Do not</emph>
                    fasten to the cover at this time.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the defroster cover (with air deflectors) on the cowl panel.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the air deflectors in the defroster cover opening. Hold the air deflector in
                    position and drill two holes thru the deflector in the location of the holes drilled in step 18
                    above. Repeat this operation on the other deflector.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f9016088" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9016088.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px"/>
                <caption>Figure 8. Template Installed Over Deflector Opening</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f9016089" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9016089.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px"/>
                <caption>Figure 9. Left Deflector Installed</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f901608a" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G901608A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px"/>
                <caption>Figure 10. Right Deflector Installed</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Fasten the two air deflectors to the defrost cover with dome head rivets (Item 9, Parts
                    List) and flat washers (Item 10, Parts List).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the upper and lower heater A/C ducts (Items 1 and 2, Parts List) between the
                    left hand air deflector in the defroster cover and the heater A/C duct (Figure 11). The upper end of
                    the upper duct (Item 1, Parts List) has a sealing ring which snaps into and properly locates it in
                    the deflector. Secure the lower heater duct to the heater A/C duct with a special hi-low screw (Item
                    5, Parts List).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f901608b" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G901608B.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px"/>
                <caption>Figure 11. Heater A/C Duct Installation</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the three electrical connectors plus the air and oil lines to the back of the
                    instrument cluster, attach the instrument cluster to the dash with four screws.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the left side dash panel cover.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the ash tray track, light with harness and ash tray.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the right side and lower right dash panel covers.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
